  "datePublished": "2026-04-03",
  "description": "A survey of the Black radical tradition's theory of governance: that governance systems carry racial inheritance, that formal equality within inherited structures reproduces domination, that abolition is a positive governance theory (replacing life-denying institutions with life-affirming ones), and that fugitivity and collective refusal are normative practices outside state capture.",
  "name": "Black Radical Governance",
